              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="The Zephyr RTOS shall provide a kernel object that implements a traditional first in, first out (FIFO) queue, allowing threads and ISRs to add and remove a limited number of 32-bit data values.">
              <DEFINITION>
                <ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>REQUIREMENT_26666e088fd749718fd78021c5ff5b6e_ReqIF.Text</ATTRIBUTE-DEFINITION-STRING-REF>
              </DEFINITION>
            </ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING>
            <ATTRIBUTE-VALUE-STRING THE-VALUE="As a Zephyr RTOS user I want to be able to exchange 1 to N data objects between different threads and ISR in a thread-safe manner with a first-in-first-out (queue) behaviour.">
